Teenspace
Privacy Policy
This policy was last updated on January 29, 2025. The practices described herein fully align with the requirements for working with teens. This privacy policy is solely for teen participants.  All other users should review the general privacy policy found
here
.
Talkspace takes your privacy seriously, and we want you to know how we collect, use, share and protect your information. In this policy, we use  the words “Personally Identifying Information" to mean information could identify you such as name and email. “Medical information” means any information that:
identifies you; and
relates to your past, present, or future physical or mental health, treatment, the provision of health care services or payment for treatment.
This includes your medical history, diagnoses, treatments, current medical condition, and use of prescription medications.
‍
Our Policy on Sales and Sharing of Personal Information
:
Your personally identifying information  and your medical information will NOT be used for marketing, commercial, or advertising purposes.
You will NOT be asked to use your personally identifying information (such as name and email) and your medical information for marketing, commercial, or advertising purposes. You may be asked to provide testimonials or participate in surveys to provide feedback on the services.
Your personally identifying information and your medical information (such as diagnosis) will NOT be sold.
Talkspace will only use your personally identifying information and medical information to provide services or to help us improve the services provided to you.
No personally identifying information and no medical information will be used for marketing or other commercial purposes; nor will your personally identifying information be given to other parties to use for marketing or commercial purposes.
Our Retention Policy
We will keep your personally identifying information and your medical information for as long as we are required by the law, to provide you with therapy or to provide support if there is a question or concern raised.
If you do not receive parental consent, an exemption from your provider within 30 days of registration, or did not meet with a therapist to talk about an exemption, Talkspace will permanently delete any personally identifying information you provided to Teenspace and you will not be contacted unless you resume the registration process.
‍
What is included in this Policy?
You can access our platform through the website
https://www.talkspace.com
or through our mobile application on
iOS
or
Android
available in the app stores.
When you sign up for Talkspace we keep and protect the privacy and security of  the personally identifying information and medical information that you provide to us or your therapist as well as any medical information that Talkspace therapists provide to you through our platform (such as information about your diagnosis or treatment).
If you are in the US your medical information is called protected health information ("
PHI
") and is protected by state and federal laws including the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996, as amended (“
HIPAA
”), and the applicable provisions of the Health Information Technology for Economic and Clinical Health (“
HITECH
”) Act. In addition to the Teenspace Privacy Policy, the HIPAA Notice of Privacy Practices, the Talkspace Privacy Policy and the Rules for Using the Talkspace Application  also has important information about privacy at Talkspace. In the event of a conflict between the
Talkspace Privacy Policy
and the
Rules for Using the Talkspace Application
, the Teenspace Privacy Policy will supersede.
If you don’t feel comfortable with the ways we use you personally identifying information in order to deliver our Services, please do not use the Services.
