How can I access, delete, or modify my personally identifiable and medical information?
You may have the right to access, correct, or delete your personally identifiable information and your medical information. We will honor your request regardless of where you live or are physically located unless a legal requirement prevents us from doing so or a legal exception applies. You can ask for any of these by using the forms below or by reaching out to
privacy@talkspace.com
.
Request to access your medical record (
Authorization for Release of Information
)
Request to send your medical record to someone else (
Third Party Authorization for Release of Confidential Information
)
Request to have your personally identifiable information deleted/removed (
Request for Information Deletion/Removal
)
We will not discriminate against you if you decide to exercise your privacy rights.
Safety and Security
We verify accounts and activity, and promote safety and security on and off our Services, such as by investigating suspicious activity or violations of our
Rules for Using the Talkspace Application
, and to ensure our Services are being used legally.
Please also note that personally identifiable and medical information we hold and information that you share may be passed to your place of study, the appropriate authorities or regulators where: this is required or requested by the authorities or by law; we have concerns that any individual is likely to cause harm to themselves or other people; or there is an actual or suspected case of illegal activity and we are requested by appropriate authorities to provide such information or cooperate with their investigation. We will not disclose your reproductive health information with anyone for the purpose of investigating or prosecuting you or another person for seeking, obtaining, providing, or facilitating lawful reproductive health care.
We will do our part to protect your personally identifiable and medical information, but it is important for you to protect your information as well. In addition, we do not control the actions of anyone with whom you or any other Talkspace user may choose to share information. As such, you should be cautious about the access you provide to others when using Talkspace, and the information you choose to share when using the Talkspace website or App.  Please be aware that no security measures are perfect or impenetrable and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.
